<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,418]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,151,177]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[328,606,152,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perdecorus">
<emphasis box="[328,606,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Petrolisthes perdecorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the other Indo-West Pacific species of the genus by having the carapace with protogastric lobes each bearing a spine at the lateral extremity, distinctly trilobate rostrum armed with marginal spines (
<figureCitation box="[599,669,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="26.[151,255,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[173,1403,354,1478]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,332,1498]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 8. Petrolisthes militaris (Heller, 1862), male, CL 10.0 mm, New Caledonia, Maitre Islet (A, B); Petrolisthes scabriculus (Dana, 1852), male, CL 7.6 mm, New Caledonia, Maitre Islet (C, D); Petrolisthes perdecorus Haig, 1981, male, CL 4.8 mm, Loyalty Islands, St. 1410 (E). A, C, rostrum and right ocular peduncle, dorsal view; B, D, left cheliped (marginal setae drawn as simplified, short plumose setae on transverse ridges omitted); E, rostrum and ocular and antennal peduncles, dorsal view. Scales equal 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/178048/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<number box="[655,669,232,258]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
E), and carpi of the chelipeds with scattered small spines on the dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,151,418]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,359,311,337]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[368,647,312,337]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perdecorus">
<emphasis box="[368,647,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Petrolisthes perdecorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded only from 
<collectingCountry box="[947,1139,312,338]" name="United States Pacific Island Wildlife Refuges" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Howland Island</collectingCountry>
, located just north of the equator in the central Pacific (
<bibRefCitation author="Haig" box="[506,649,352,378]" pageId="27" pageNumber="46" refString="Haig, J. (1981 a) Three new species of Petrolisthes (Decapoda, Anomura, Porcellanidae) from the Indo-West Pacific. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 1, 265 - 271." type="journal article" year="1981" yearSuffix="a">
Haig 
<number box="[572,634,352,378]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" value="1981.0">1981</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the second record of the species, collected from depths of 
<quantity box="[151,240,392,418]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="m" value="16.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="2.0">2–30 m</quantity>
in the Loyalty Islands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
